In the first simulation, we set $K=2$ and $f_1=25Hz,f_2=50Hz$. If we use ESPRIT for S1, we will get a series of eligible frequencies, namely $5Hz, 25Hz, 45Hz, 10Hz, 30Hz, 50Hz$. Any two sequences are selected to obtain the eligible frequencies from one sequence via ESPRIT and the pseudo-spectrum of the eligible frequencies from the other sequence via the MUSIC-like algorithm. The results obtained from S1,S2 and S1,S3 and S2,S3 are all shown in Fig.~\ref{fig2}. Because $f_2-f_1=5\cdot f_H/ab$, the result obtained from S1,S2 is not able to recognize the correct frequencies as shown in Fig.~\ref{fig2}(a). While in Fig.~\ref{fig2}(b) and Fig.~\ref{fig2}(c), the correct frequencies are found. The results accord with our previous analysis.
